The paper deals with curriculum learning in reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of Markov Decision Processes, which is a common tool in reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions natural language processing and computer vision as potential domains for evaluating the approach, which suggests that cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are also possible sub-categories.
